Global Waste Paper Reuse Market Insights
Waste Paper Reuse Market size was valued at USD 75 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 120 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.0% from 2024 to 2030.

Waste Paper Reuse Market Overview
The global waste paper reuse market is a rapidly growing sector, driven by increasing environmental awareness and the rising demand for sustainable packaging and recycled paper products. The market size is valued at approximately USD 40 billion in 2024 and is expected to expand at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2025 to 2030. The recycling of waste paper reduces the need for virgin wood fibers, leading to lower deforestation rates and environmental degradation. With increasing government regulations and growing eco-friendly initiatives across industries, the market is poised for significant growth in the coming years.

